1. *Policijom* upravlja Ministarstvo unutrašnjih poslova. (The police is managed by the Ministry of Interior.)
2. Potrebno je da se *policijom* upravlja profesionalno i po zakonu. (It is necessary to manage the police professionally and according to the law.)
3. Građani mogu da se obrate *policiji* u slučaju problema. (Citizens can turn to the police in case of problems.)
4. Nakon krađe, žrtva je pozvala *policiju* da prijavi incident. (After the theft, the victim called the police to report the incident.)
5. *Policija* je intervenisala na ulici zbog saobraćajnog prekršaja. (The police intervened on the street due to a traffic violation.)
6. Na ulici su vidljivi pripadnici *policije* u uniformama. (Police officers in uniforms are visible on the street.)
7. Ulice su blokirane zbog protesta, a *policija* je obezbeđuje. (The streets are blocked due to the protest, and the police are securing them.)
8. *Policajac* je zaustavio vozača zbog prekoračenja brzine. (The police officer stopped the driver for speeding.)
9. *Policajci* su priveli osumnjičenog u vezi sa pljačkom. (The police arrested a suspect in connection with the robbery.)
10. *Policajka* je izašla iz vozila da reguliše saobraćaj. (The policewoman got out of the vehicle to regulate traffic.)